Just wanna add in tips here for anyone going to try these.. best to not use weights for those having not exercised for a long time. Stretch before the exercise. For the one with the mop, the whole point is to get your knees above the waist and to get your knees higher, tighten your stomach (core) muscles and keep your back straight. Also land on the balls of the feet. For the one with the bottles, if cant do then put out which ever leg you're more comfortable with first and go into a lunge position. Make sure the knee doesn't go over your toes, so keep it best at 90° angle and lean your weight onto the heel. Then put your legs back together in standing position and lunge on the other leg. Remember to keep the back straight. And for any jumps always bend the knees to protect the joint
